com.SIMRacingApps

Interface Connector.Callback

  • Enclosing class:
    Connector

    public static interface Connector.Callback
    This interface is used to call back to your implementation as data is received. The methods are called in the same thread that the Connector.run(Callback) method was invoked in. Each method should return true to continue to process data. Returning false will cause the Connector.run(Callback) to return.

    • Method Detail

      • DataReady

        boolean DataReady(Connector connector,
                  java.lang.Integer ips)
           throws Connector.ConnectorException
        Called when data is ready to be used. Time spent in this call should be less than 16ms to prevent packet loss because this routine is single threaded with the SIMs notification event.
        Parameters:
        connector - The connector.
        ips - The current iterations per second(IPS) value.
        Returns:
        true to continue receiving data, false to stop
        Throws:
        Connector.ConnectorException - An problem occurred in the Connector

      • Waiting

        boolean Waiting(Connector connector)
         throws Connector.ConnectorException
        Called when the connector is not getting data from the SIM. But, you are still able to call methods on the connector to get data anyway, it just might be stale data or what the SIM wants you to get when the SIM is not running.
        Parameters:
        connector - The connector.
        Returns:
        true to continue receiving data, false to stop
        Throws:
        Connector.ConnectorException - If a problem occurred in the Connector
